The paper discusses the development of autonomous systems and the challenges that need to be addressed before they become commonplace engineering practice. The paper focuses on decision-making as a central aspect of autonomous systems and discusses challenges related to specifying behavior, simulation and analysis, and engineering systems that combine model-driven and machine learning techniques. This suggests that the paper belongs to the Software Engineering (cs.SE), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Robotics (cs.RO), Systems and Control (cs.SY), and Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-categories.
